Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the @dried linguine{180%g}.

When boiling, add the linguine then bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot (off the heat).

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

While the linguine cooks, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%g}(halved).

Place a large pan over medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @chorizo{100%g} until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%mins}.

Add the onion and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Fry until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{3-4%mins}.

Add garlic, tomatoes, @sugar{½%tsp} and another pinch of salt. Fry until tomatoes are softened, ~{6-7%mins}.

Add the @passata{1%pack} and @creme fraiche{110%g}. Simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%mins}. Season to taste with salt, pepper and sugar.

Loosen the sauce with a splash of @water{to taste} if necessary.

Toss the linguine through the sauce to coat and warm through.

Divide your pasta between deep #plates{} or #bowls{}.

Finish with a sprinkling of @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%g}.